pip install virtualenv (command)
virtualenv env (command)
Set-ExecutionPolicy unrestricted (A) in windows powershell (command)
now envoirnment created now we have to activate the virtual envoirnment. env tab S tab act tab .ps1

<!-- # making a to do app using flask



<!-- now we are creating a database class -->

a class contain what to store.
which database to use.
which fields to create
which integer which string etc.
a kind of schema.

<!-- to install sql alchemy-->

pip install flask-sqlalchemy

<!-- iporting from flask -->

from flask_sqlalchemy import SQLAlchemy

<!-- using for mysql or sql lite from alchemy docuimetation -->
<!-- here using sqllite -->

app.config['SQLALCHEMY_DATABASE_URI'] = 'sqlite:///test.db'

Add with app.app_context(): above db = SQLAlchemy(app) like this:

with app.app_context():
db = SQLAlchemy(app)

and when using the commands do this:

python

> > > from app import app, db
> > > app.app_context().push()
> > > db.create_all()

This will create the database in a folder called instance. After that everything just works fine. :)

